originalText.text: John, Martin, Christian, Ebony...all amazing trainers.  Top notch.  Watching them with clients and working with John and Martin has boosted my self esteem.  Seeing them remain humble in such a prestige gym is top notch service.  They are engaging, considerate, effective, humble, efficient, and respectful.  They have more faith in their clients than the clients probably have in themselves.  As much as I despise working out, I enjoy coming in and feeling encouraged to move forward.  John is my personal trainer, but ben when he is not around, the others always say a few words of encouragement (especially at 7am when I do NOT want to be there).  If you're looking for a prestige gym, with professional but down to earth staff, look no further!

originalText.text:
Top tier equinox facility. I love their functional fitness floor. All their trainers are friendly, as is the front desk staff and all are very helpful. The cleaning staff does a great job at keeping it clean and well run.

Management switches up the equipment location and removes equipment sometimes and doesn’t inform the trainers. I’ve messaged management asking abt this sometimes and they are not helpful and have been rude. Management aside, the staff and the people you see working here are wonderful.

Also yoga room is starting to smell too much like feet. Can we please have some spray or scents candle in that??

Much appreciated. Will be happier keep paying 300 fat bucks if those two things get fixed :)

originalText.text:
I will happily travel 45 min by train and bus one-way to go to this location on a weekend. Doesn’t feel overcrowded to me in the locker / gym area on a Saturday from 11am-2pm when I go.

Shoutout to the front desk staff who are so friendly and helpful every time I have a question or issue (and I don’t feel stupid for asking). This is one of my favorite Equinox clubs in NYC because the front desk staff are so nice - even though not my home gym - plus I like James’ barre classes here a lot as someone who appreciates the musicality aspect in group fitness, moving to the beat of music, while doing low-impact exercises blended with ballet, easy to follow yet challenging, and James style is motivational, strict but not aggressive, and creative with the combinations of moves. I have a ton of fun in his class every time

originalText.text: Best Equinox in NYC -- teachers are out of this world: Esco (Yoga), Elgin (Pilates), James/Emily/Kevin (Barre). I go every day + always impressed by the check-in desk, cleanliness of studios + nice hospitality staff.
